---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---

<ProjectLayout
  title="Multi-Tenant Workspace"
  subtitle="SaaS Platform Architecture"
  description="A Slack-inspired multi-tenant backend with schema-per-tenant PostgreSQL, workspace-scoped RBAC, and production-grade tenant isolation."
  github="https://github.com/carissaayo/multi-tenancy-backend"
  tags={['NestJS', 'PostgreSQL', 'Redis', 'BullMQ', 'MinIO', 'TypeORM', 'Passport.js']}
>
  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      A Slack-inspired, multi-tenant backend system designed to demonstrate real-world SaaS
      architecture, strict tenant isolation, and scalable backend design. Each workspace is
      a tenant, fully isolated at the data and authorization layers, while sharing a single
      application and infrastructure.
    </p>
    <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
      A single user can belong to multiple workspaces with different roles, mirroring how
      production collaboration platforms work. This project focuses on architecture,
      correctness, and scalability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Architecture</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>Client (Web / Mobile)
         │
    Load Balancer / API Gateway
         │
    Workspace Resolver (Tenant Middleware)
         │
    Authentication (JWT)
         │
    Authorization (Workspace RBAC)
         │
    Business Logic (Channels / Messages / Members)
         │
    Tenant-Scoped Database Access
         │
    Usage Tracking & Feature Flags
         │
    Response</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-4">Core Concepts</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="p-5 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-zinc-200 font-semibold mb-3">Tenant Model</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-300">Tenant = Workspace</strong></span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span>Identified via subdomain (<code class="font-mono text-cyan-400 text-xs">acme.app.com</code>)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span>Fallbacks: headers and JWT claims</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span>All data access is workspace-scoped</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-zinc-200 font-semibold mb-3">Identity Model</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-300">User</strong> = global identity</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-zinc-300">WorkspaceMember</strong> = scoped role & permissions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span>Users can belong to multiple workspaces</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 mt-0.5">&#8250;</span>
            <span>Different roles per workspace</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Key Engineering Decisions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Schema-Per-Tenant Isolation</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Each workspace gets its own PostgreSQL schema within a shared database. This provides
          strong data isolation, easy per-tenant auditing, and shared connection pooling without
          the operational overhead of database-per-tenant.
        </p>
        <div class="architecture-block text-xs">
          <pre><code>workspace_acme.channels
workspace_acme.messages
workspace_acme.members

workspace_globex.channels
workspace_globex.messages
workspace_globex.members</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Why Schema-Per-Tenant over Alternatives</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Approach</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Isolation</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Ops Cost</th>
                <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Scale</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
              <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">Shared tables (row-level)</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Weak</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Low</td>
                <td class="py-3">High</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50 bg-zinc-800/20">
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-cyan-400">Schema-per-tenant (chosen)</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Strong</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Medium</td>
                <td class="py-3">High</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4 text-zinc-300">Database-per-tenant</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">Strongest</td>
                <td class="py-3 pr-4">High</td>
                <td class="py-3">Limited</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Workspace-Scoped RBAC</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Roles are workspace-scoped, not global. A user can be an Owner in one workspace and
          a Guest in another. The authorization layer checks workspace membership and role
          before every operation.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
          <div class="p-3 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-lg text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-200">Owner</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">Full control</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-lg text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-200">Admin</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">Manage workspace</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-lg text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-200">Member</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">Standard access</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-zinc-900/50 border border-zinc-800/80 rounded-lg text-center">
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-200">Guest</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">Read-only</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Consistent Request Flow</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Every request follows the same pipeline. This consistency makes the system predictable
          and auditable:
        </p>
        <ol class="space-y-2 text-zinc-400 text-sm">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">1.</span>
            <span>Resolve workspace from subdomain/header</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">2.</span>
            <span>Validate JWT</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">3.</span>
            <span>Verify workspace membership</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">4.</span>
            <span>Check resource-level permissions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">5.</span>
            <span>Execute business logic in tenant schema</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">6.</span>
            <span>Emit notification events</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">7.</span>
            <span>Track usage metrics</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-cyan-400 font-mono shrink-0">8.</span>
            <span>Return response</span>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mb-2">Feature Flags & Plans</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Workspace plans control feature access: message history limits, file storage limits,
          and advanced features (audit logs, integrations). Feature checks occur before
          business logic execution, not after. This prevents wasted computation and provides
          clear upgrade signals to users.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Technology Stack</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <th class="text-left py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Layer</th>
            <th class="text-left py-3 text-zinc-400 font-mono font-normal">Technology</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-zinc-400">
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Backend Framework</td>
            <td class="py-3">NestJS</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Database</td>
            <td class="py-3">PostgreSQL (schema-per-tenant)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">ORM</td>
            <td class="py-3">TypeORM</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Cache / Counters</td>
            <td class="py-3">Redis</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Background Jobs</td>
            <td class="py-3">BullMQ</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">File Storage</td>
            <td class="py-3">MinIO (S3-compatible)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">Auth</td>
            <td class="py-3">Passport.js + JWT</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-6 text-zinc-300">API Docs</td>
            <td class="py-3">Swagger / OpenAPI</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">What This Project Demonstrates</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Real multi-tenant SaaS design (not demo CRUD)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Correct isolation boundaries</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Clean authorization modeling</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Production-grade NestJS structure</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Trade-off awareness (schema vs database per tenant)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 bg-zinc-900/30 rounded-lg">
        <span class="text-cyan-400 text-lg leading-none">&#10003;</span>
        <span class="text-zinc-300 text-sm">Usage tracking and billing foundations</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Module Structure</h2>
    <div class="architecture-block">
      <pre><code>src/
├── core/
│   ├── tenant/            # Workspace resolution middleware
│   ├── auth/              # JWT authentication
│   ├── rbac/              # Workspace roles & permissions
│   ├── feature-flags/     # Plan-based access control
│   └── usage/             # Metrics & limits
│
├── workspaces/            # Workspace CRUD, schema provisioning
├── members/               # Membership management, invitations
├── channels/              # Channel CRUD, member management
├── messages/              # Message persistence, thread support
├── files/                 # MinIO upload, workspace-scoped storage
└── notifications/         # Event emission, delivery</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProjectLayout>
